{
  "doc_id": "32283",
  "text": "In a recent study it has been shown that pancreas transplantation in diabetic rats results in denervated, well vascularized insulin secretory tissue which could only be stimulated by humoral factors. After ingestion of food the preabsorptive insulin response was absent [CITATION_1] . This finding has also been confirmed by others [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
